# Storybook Component Structure (Design System)

For every new component story in `apps/docs/src/stories/*.stories.ts`, keep this structure aligned with the current Button Primary implementation:

1. `Playground` story with interactive controls.
2. `States` story in Figma-style exhibit format:
   - Left side: `artwork` canvas preview (white background) showing component render.
   - Right side: state title + concise attributes/spec text.
   - Keep state title compact (small heading style; approximately half of large display size used in early prototypes).
   - Do not repeat the component name inside each state detail block when the component context is already clear from the story title.
   - Must explicitly include supported sizes in each state block (for example `Sizes: Sm, Md`).
   - Must document the key visual token(s) per state (for example background, text, border/focus).
   - Recommended state set (when applicable): `Default`, `Hover`, `Pressed`, `Disabled`, `Focus`.
   - Keep Figma enum naming exactly as defined for each component (for example `Focus` vs `Focused`).
3. `Anatomy` story including:
   - `Figma live reference` section with:
     - direct Figma link to the source node
     - embedded Figma iframe (`https://www.figma.com/embed?...`)
   - `Visual reference` section with rendered component variants on white preview canvas
   - `Measurements` section with concrete values (padding, gap, radius, sizing, typography)
   - `Blueprint` section with inspect-style visual annotations + attribute list

Implementation notes:
- Reuse shared DS classes in `design-system.css` when possible.
- Keep spacing and heading hierarchy consistent with existing foundations/component docs.
- Avoid hardcoded one-off inline styles when equivalent reusable CSS classes can be created.
- Keep `States` and `Anatomy` nomenclature consistent across components for predictable docs navigation.
